# MorseReverseShell
Reverse shell 64bit shellcode, in different format. Replace your onw IP address, port is fixed to 443.

IP address must be in this format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx fx. 010.010.010.010 three digits pr. octet.

IP address 192.168.001.100 become " /         /  ? /      /        ?-/-/ ? /-/-?"

space equals one
/ means new digit
- is zero
? means end of number

in C# code:

```
        string Octet1 = " /         /  ?";      // 192 
        string Octet2 = " /      /        ?";   // 168
        string Octet3 = "-/-/ ?";               // 001
        string Octet4 = " /-/-?";               // 100
```
